  "title": "Focus (of a fixed lens)",
  "parse": {
    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>2-2-105</b>\n</p><p>The point of intersection of the axis of the lens (2-2-115) and the median horizontal plane through the belt. <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span> ray of light emitted by a point source situated at this point is re-directed by an element of the lens into a direction normal to the axis of the lens. (Figs. 16b and 18)\n</p><p><br>\nNote: The term \"focus\" in its more general and correct sense is given in 2-1-125.\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-image-border\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch2_Fig16b.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/c/c8/Ch2_Fig16b.jpg/400px-Ch2_Fig16b.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"243\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/c/c8/Ch2_Fig16b.jpg/600px-Ch2_Fig16b.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/c/c8/Ch2_Fig16b.jpg/800px-Ch2_Fig16b.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-image-border\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch2_Fig18.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/7/75/Ch2_Fig18.jpg/400px-Ch2_Fig18.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"176\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/7/75/Ch2_Fig18.jpg/600px-Ch2_Fig18.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/7/75/Ch2_Fig18.jpg/800px-Ch2_Fig18.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p><br>\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>ampere\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615175513\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.037 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.046 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 816/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 307/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   13.506      1 -total\n 73.35%    9.907      1 Template:Languages\n 48.29%    6.522      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 25.64%    3.463      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:522-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615175513 and revision id 9507. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->